UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1918
1 AN ACT relating to Medicaid waiver program coverage for community interveners.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 205 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) As used in this section, "community intervener" means a trained service provider
6 who assists an individual who is deaf-blind to access communication,
7 environmental information, and community activities through tactile, visual,
8 auditory, or other individualized methods, for the purpose of supporting
9 independent living, self-determination, and full participation in home and
10 community-based settings.
11 (2) (a) If approved by the federal Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services,
12 community interveners shall be a recognized provider type within the
13 Michelle P. waiver program, and the Michelle P. waiver program shall
14 provide coverage for community intervener services for deaf-blind
15 individuals.
16 (b) The Department for Medicaid Services shall, within ninety (90) days after
17 receiving approval from the federal Centers for Medicare and Medicaid
18 Services to cover community intervener services in the Michelle P. waiver
19 program, promulgate administrative regulations in accordance with KRS
20 Chapter 13A to implement this section, including but not limited to:
21 1. Training and qualification requirements for community interveners;
22 2. The provider enrollment process for community interveners;
23 3. Services that community interveners are permitted to provide; and
24 4. Reimbursement rates for services provided by a community intervener.
25 Section 2. If the Cabinet for Health and Family Services or the Department for
26 Medicaid Services determines that a state plan amendment, waiver, or any other form of
27 authorization or approval from any federal agency to implement Section 1 of this Act is
Page 1 of 2
